[{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"CurrentModule = TheNumberLine\n\nusing PlutoUI\n\nmacro bind(def, element) # hide\n    quote\n        local iv = try Base.loaded_modules[Base.PkgId(Base.UUID(\"6e696c72-6542-2067-7265-42206c756150\"), \"AbstractPlutoDingetjes\")].Bonds.initial_value catch; b -> missing; end\n        local el = $(esc(element))\n        global $(esc(def)) = Core.applicable(Base.get, el) ? Base.get(el) : iv(el)\n        el\n    end\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/#User-Directions","page":"Docs","title":"User Directions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/#1.-Open-Cloud","page":"Docs","title":"1. Open Cloud","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"You can try TheNumberLine.jl in the cloud without having to install anything.","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"(Image: Dev)","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/#2.-Private-Computer","page":"Docs","title":"2. Private Computer","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"If instead you want to use TheNumberLine.jl then proceed as follows.","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"Download TheNumberLine.jl\nOpen a terminal window go to the TheNumberLine.jl/src/ folder\nStart Pluto.jl e.g. via julia -e \"using Pluto; Pluto.run()\"\nIn web browser window, select and open standard_number_line.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"tip: Tip\nSome tips for new users are provided below.","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"To use TheNumberLine.jl on your own computer, you'll need to download Julia itself beforehand.\nto close the session you want to go back to the terminal window and Press Ctrl+C","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/#Main-Functions","page":"Docs","title":"Main Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"NumberLinePlot\nNumberLineExpression\nmake_hist\nsave_hist","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/#TheNumberLine.NumberLinePlot","page":"Docs","title":"TheNumberLine.NumberLinePlot","text":"NumberLinePlot(y; path=tempdir(), filename=\"tmp.png\")\n\nDisplay the number line sequence of operations, defined by vector y, as a graph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"functions/#TheNumberLine.NumberLineExpression","page":"Docs","title":"TheNumberLine.NumberLineExpression","text":"NumberLineExpression(x)\n\nDisplay the number line sequence of operations, defined by vector x, as text.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"functions/#TheNumberLine.make_hist","page":"Docs","title":"TheNumberLine.make_hist","text":"make_hist(;max_value=5.0,max_count=5,aspect_ratio=2.0)\n\nfig=make_hist()\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"functions/#TheNumberLine.save_hist","page":"Docs","title":"TheNumberLine.save_hist","text":"save_hist(fig::Makie.Figure;file=joinpath(tempdir(),\"histogram_template.png\"))\n\nsave_hist(make_hist())\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"functions/#Various","page":"Docs","title":"Various","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/#1.-Use-a-Slider","page":"Docs","title":"1. Use a Slider","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"In the first code cell of standard_number_line.jl, where values are entered, you can use a list of a slider or multiple choice instead.","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"To do this, replace the line that says","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"` Type value : ` $(@bind b html\"<input type=text>\")","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"with","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"`Select value of x from the list : ` $(@bind b Select([\"4\",\"3\",\"2\",\"1\",\"0\",\"-1\",\"-2\",\"-3\",\"-4\"],default=\"0\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"or","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"`Choose value of x using slider : ` $(@bind b aSlider(-10:10; default=0))","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/#2.-Integers-Only","page":"Docs","title":"2. Integers Only","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"To restrict the number line to using integers (as opposed to reals), try changing TestType in standard_number_line.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"To do this, replace the line that says","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"TestType=Number; NumberLineType=Float64; \"Number LineType = $(NumberLineType)\"","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"with ","category":"page"},{"location":"functions/","page":"Docs","title":"Docs","text":"TestType=Int; NumberLineType=Int; \"NumberLineType = $(NumberLineType)\"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = TheNumberLine\n\nusing PlutoUI\n\nmacro bind(def, element) # hide\n    quote\n        local iv = try Base.loaded_modules[Base.PkgId(Base.UUID(\"6e696c72-6542-2067-7265-42206c756150\"), \"AbstractPlutoDingetjes\")].Bonds.initial_value catch; b -> missing; end\n        local el = $(esc(element))\n        global $(esc(def)) = Core.applicable(Base.get, el) ? Base.get(el) : iv(el)\n        el\n    end\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#TheNumberLine.jl","page":"Home","title":"TheNumberLine.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The Number Line is a common teaching tool in e.g. K-12 math classes accross the U.S.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Authors: Gael Forget and Jane Chapin","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: DOI)","category":"page"},{"location":"#The-Random-Turtle","page":"Home","title":"The Random Turtle","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the random turtle activity we take a series of N consecutive, random, steps on the number line. Each step is either -1 (left) or +1 (right) based on a coin flip. We do this N times in a row (10 times for example) and observe our final value at the end (green arrow). All you need to do this is copy the following line to a new code cell and run it:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"import TheNumberLine: NumberLinePlot # hide\nNumberLinePlot(rand((-1,1),10),path=\".\",filename=\"RandomTurtle.png\")\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The activity basically is do this a bunch of times and discuss how results can vary .","category":"page"},{"location":"#Interactive-Use","page":"Home","title":"Interactive Use","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In your web-browser (see User Directions for detail) :","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"type a number in the text box\nclick on the add button\nrepeat or reset","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Repeat a few times, e.g. with other numbers, to obtain something like the image shown above. You can also hit start over at any point.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Histograms","page":"Home","title":"Histograms","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This module provides a simple way to create an empty histogram that students can print and write over.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"import TheNumberLine: make_hist, save_hist # hide\nsave_hist(make_hist(),file=\"hist.png\")\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"#Notebook-Example","page":"Home","title":"Notebook Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"standard_number_line.html\nstandard_number_line.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"#School-Day-Table","page":"Home","title":"School Day Table","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"table_school_days.html\ntable_school_days.jl","category":"page"}]
